The fire broke out at 7pm on Thursday, October 28. [Mate Tongola, Standard]  A huge fire broke out in Kanzokea Forest in Kangundo, Machakos County on Thursday night, October 28.  Kangundo Central Member of County Assembly Moses Musyoka told The Standard that the fire, whose cause is unknown, started at around 7pm, consuming everything on its path.  “It’s currently dry in Machakos. As a result, the fire spread so fast as it burnt dry leaves and twigs,” said Musyoka.  Efforts by the Machakos firefighting team to put out the inferno were futile.  Machakos man who stabbed wife six times surrenders to police  Alfred Mutua opens up on Boniface Mwangi beef, marital split and State House  Alfred Mutua: Kalonzo Musyoka no longer the kingpin after election loss  Athi River and its contaminated vegetables  It is suspected that a small fire lit in a homestead neighbouring the forest spread into the woodlands, resulting in the massive destruction.  No casualties were reported during the incident, police said.  Kanzokea Forest is one of the gazetted water catchment areas in Machakos County.  As of the time of publishing this story, the fire was still raging.   Machakos Decides: Candidates make their final pitches, low-key last day due to rallies ban  Wiper Campaigns: Party changes strategy in Machakos, it will use pass-by parades  Wiper, ANC, KANU and Ford-K parties vow to work together in order to defeat Ruto's UDA in Machakos By Lynn Kolongei | 20 hours ago By Winfrey Owino | 1 day ago By Jael Mboga | 3 days ago By Mireri Junior | 4 days ago